{
  "texts": [
    "As we shall see, in the scenario A of the ABCD model the upper bounds on the last four channels play a hierarchical role in constraining the branching ratios of LFV B and B s decays.",
    "Their combined effect prevents the branching fractions of LFV B and B s decays from exceeding O(10 -12).It is useful to analyse the individual constraints from the four leptonic processes, which in scenarios different from scenario A depend on distinct parameters.",
    "This provides us with a guidance on possible modifications of the scenario.",
    "For instance, since τ -→ µ -µ + µ -provides the weakest constraint, one may consider assigning a different role to the third lepton family compared to the other two: we defer such an investigation to future work.",
    "In the following we analyze the impact of τ -→ µ -µ + µ -and µ -→ e -γ, then we consider the most stringent channels µ -→ e -e + e -and µ -→ e -conversion in nuclei."
  ]
}